text: A patient with stage 2 हृदय रोग underwent an emergency Angioplasty procedure due to severe chest pain and बुखार after an abnormal Lipid Profile report.

A 35-year-old patient, diagnosed with मधुमेह (Diabetes) and हृदय रोग (Cardiac disease), was administered 5mg Metformin and 20mg Atorvastatin daily after a routine ब्लड टेस्ट (Blood test) and ECG report.
Patient was diagnosed with stage 2 हृदय रोग and prescribed 25mg Metoprolol twice daily after a chest pain episode and abnormal lipid profile report.
The patient with तेज़ बुखार and सिर दर्द underwent an urgent CT scan and was prescribed 500mg Paracetamol twice daily for 5 days.
Patient को तेज़ बुखार और सिर दर्द के साथ Angioplasty के बाद 5mg Aspirin और 200mL IV fluids दिए गए, लेकिन उन्हें ECG और Blood Test के लिए भेजा गया।
The patient with type 2 मधुमेह was admitted to the ICU for सीने में दर्द and underwent an emergency Angioplasty after a cardiac arrest, and was prescribed 10mg Aspirin and 40mg Atorvastatin daily.
The patient who underwent Angioplasty was prescribed 5mg Aspirin twice daily to manage हृदय रोग and was advised to undergo a monthly Lipid Profile ब्लड टेस्ट to monitor cholesterol levels.
Patient को तेज़ सिर दर्द और बुखार था, इसलिए doctor ने उसे 5mg Paracetamol और एक ब्लड टेस्ट कराने के लिए कहा।
Patient with stage 2 डायबिटीज़ was admitted to ICU for severe हाइपोग्लाइसीमिया after an abnormal लिपिड प्रोफाइल report and was prescribed 5mg Glimepiride twice daily.
A patient with chronic हृदय रोग underwent an emergency angioplasty due to severe chest pain and तेज़ बुखार after a series of ECG and blood tests.
Patient को तेज़ बुखार और सिरदर्द के बाद emergency ward में भर्ती किया गया और immediate परीक्षण के लिए 200mL ब्लड सैंपल लिया गया जिसमें ECG और Lipid Profile भी शामिल था।

A patient with stage 2 मधुमेह was advised to undergo an Angioplasty procedure after a series of tests, including a ब्लड टेस्ट and ECG, revealed abnormal results, and was prescribed 20mg Atorvastatin and 10 units of Insulin daily.

The patient with दिल की बीमारी underwent an emergency Angioplasty procedure after a series of abnormal ECG and ब्लड टेस्ट reports, and was prescribed 20mg Atorvastatin twice daily for high cholesterol.
The patient with तेज़ बुखार and सिर दर्द underwent an emergency सीटी स्कैन and was prescribed 500mg Paracetamol twice daily for 5 days.
The patient with acute myocardial infarction, also known as दिल का दौरा, underwent an emergency coronary angiography and was prescribed 40mg Atorvastatin twice daily for high cholesterol.
The patient with severe हृदय रोग underwent an emergency Angioplasty procedure after a critical ECG report showed abnormal heart rhythms and was prescribed 100mg Aspirin daily.
The patient with तेज़ बुखार and सिर दर्द was prescribed 200mg Crocin after an abnormal ब्लड टेस्ट report.
The patient with क्रोनिक हृदय रोग underwent an emergency Angioplasty procedure after a chest pain attack and was prescribed 25mg Aspirin and Metformin for life.
The patient with stage 2 मधुमेह was prescribed 10 units of Insulin after an abnormal Lipid Profile report and ECG test to monitor तेज़ सिर दर्द and बुखार symptoms.
The patient with stage 2 मधुमेह was prescribed 20mg Metformin twice daily after an abnormal Lipid Profile report and was advised to undergo एक एमआरआई scan.
The patient with तेज़ सिर दर्द and stage 2 मधुमेह was prescribed 20mg Metformin and advised to undergo a Lipid Profile test after an abnormal ECG report.

The patient was admitted to the ICU with severe बुखार and दर्द in the chest, and underwent an emergency Angioplasty after a abnormal ECG report, and was prescribed 200mL of डोक्सिसाइक्लिन thrice daily.
The patient with stage 2 मधुमेह was prescribed 10mg Metformin twice daily after an abnormal Lipid Profile report, and was advised to undergo डायलिसिस due to severe तेज़ बुखार and पेट दर्द.
Patient with stage 2 तेज़ बुखार and severe सिर दर्द underwent an emergency CT scan and was prescribed 500mg Paracetamol thrice daily.
The patient was diagnosed with हृदय रोग and Diabetes, and was prescribed 10mg Atorvastatin and 5 units of Insulin after an abnormal Lipid Profile and ECG report due to तेज़ सिर दर्द and chest pain.
Patient को तेज़ बुखार और सिर दर्द के कारण emergency ward में भर्ती किया गया और डॉक्टर ने 500mg Paracetamol और 200mL IV fluid के साथ CPR और ECG टेस्ट किया।
Patient को तेज़ बुखार और सिर दर्द के कारण emergency ward में admit किया गया और 500mg Paracetamol दिया गया और एक abnormal किडनी फंक्शन टेस्ट के बाद डॉक्टर ने Angioplasty की सलाह दी।
Patient को तेज़ सिर दर्द और chest pain के कारण emergency ward में भर्ती किया गया और उसे ECG, ब्लड टेस्ट और 325mg Aspirin दिया गया।
The patient with acute तेज़ सिर दर्द was given 200mL IV fluids after an abnormal MRI स्कैन report showed signs of इस्केमिक स्ट्रोक.

The patient with acute myocardial infarction (दिल का दौरा) underwent अन्गिओप्लास्टी after a series of tests including ECG, ब्लड टेस्ट, and Troponin levels were found abnormal, and was prescribed 300mg Aspirin and 20mg Atorvastatin twice daily.
